FBIS3-55808 "drsov008_t_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Laar Says Government Ready for Talks With NATO LD1101172094 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1500 GMT 11 Jan 94 LD1101172094 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network Language: Estonian Article Type:BFN [Text] Prime Minister Mart Laar stated at a news conference today that within the next couple of days the government will shape an opinion about planned cooperation with NATO. According to Laar, a statement from Estonia to NATO has been drawn up and should logically bear signatures of both the president and the prime minister. Later, once a decision is taken, Estonia will be ready immediately to start talks so as to (?fulfill) a Partnership for Peace agreement with a spcific content, Laar added. According to Laar, the statement under discussion would (?serve) as a starting point for the talks. Estonia wishes to be one of the first countries to open talks with NATO with quite a specific program, art Laar added.
